   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Children with Disabilities in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MAITS Community Healthworker Empowerment Programme (CHW) will train 60 Community Healthworkers based at two centres in rural Uganda, Kyaninga Chlldren&apos;s Centre in Karabole and Kasole. Our programme will support 240 children with developmental disabilities, from cerebral palsy to autism, and 240 caregivers in  resource-poor districts where there is little access to therapeutic intervention. Our training will improve children&apos;s quality of life and independence, as well a parents/carers&apos; wellbeing.</narrative>
  </description>
